SSH Screen once logged in
Use Tethering from your Android without Root:)
Download Netshare full version from following link. After its installed use, Use
start WiFi Hotspot then on EON connect to wifi however it will say its
connected but it will be local. After that you have enter the proxy settings
manually not automatic since it wont working where on local host you will
enter the following IP address 192.168.49.1 and port 8282 and boom now you
have EON connected on the line:)
Use EON as Local Network just for SSH
Settings gear
Network
Open Tethering Settings
Toggle Portable Wi-Fi hotspot
If you want to have custom network name you can click on setup Wi-Fi
hotspot first.
Now just login using ssh using default IP of EON which is as shown on
above slides.
192.168.1.100 and port 8022
Use AIO script for custom branch
cd /data && rm -rf openpilot* && git clone
https://github.com/username/openpilot && cd openpilot && git checkout
branchname && reboot
Example
cd /data && rm -rf openpilot* && git clone
https://github.com/ghostriding/openpilot && cd openpilot && git checkout
alca_056_pedal_screenoff && reboot
